<refentry id='wmater'>

<refmeta>
  <refentrytitle>WMATER</refentrytitle>
  <manvolnum>nged</manvolnum>
  <refmiscinfo class='source'>BRL-CAD</refmiscinfo>
  <refmiscinfo class='manual'>BRL-CAD MGED Commands</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv id='name'>
  <refname>wmater</refname>
  <refpurpose>Lists the shader name and parameters, RGB color,
<emphasis>RGB_valid</emphasis> flag, and the inheritance flag to the specified <emphasis>file</emphasis> for the listed <emphasis>objects</emphasis>.
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<!-- body begins here -->
<refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
  <cmdsynopsis>
    <command>wmater</command>    
    
    <arg choice='req'><replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
    <arg choice='req'><replaceable>objects</replaceable></arg>
  </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1 id='description'>
  <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
  <para>Lists the shader name and parameters, RGB color,
<emphasis>RGB_valid</emphasis> flag, and the inheritance flag to the specified <emphasis>file</emphasis> for the listed<emphasis>objects</emphasis>. The format used is compatible with the <command>rmater</command> command. If <emphasis>file</emphasis> already exists, the new data is appended to it.
   </para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id='examples'>
  <title>EXAMPLES</title>
  <para>The example shows the use of the <command>wmater</command> command to list the shader parameters of two objects to a specified file.
  
  </para>

  <example>
    <title>List the shader parameters of two objects to a specified file.</title>
    <para>
      <prompt>mged></prompt><userinput>wmater mater_file group1 regiona</userinput>
    </para>
    <para>Lists the shader parameters of <emphasis>group1</emphasis> and <emphasis>regiona</emphasis> to <emphasis>mater_file</emphasis>.
       
    </para>
  </example>
 
</refsect1>

